text:
Travel Articles | 
Places to Visit: Mumbai is a young city and much of the land which has been comprising the city wasn’t existing until it was claimed from the sea over three centuries ago. It is a pleasant surprise to find many rock cut caves such as Elephanta, kanheri and Mahakali which are within the city limits. 

Museums and Galleries: Chhatrapati Shivaji Maharaj Vastu Sangrahalaya (Prince of Wales Museum), and the National Gallery of Modern Art. You can also plan to visit Jehangir Art Gallery, also at Kala Ghoda, displays changing exhibits by notable artists which is worth a visit. 
Beaches: Girgaon Chowpaty in S 
Zoos, parks and Gardens: Veermata Jijabai Udyan city zoo which is Byculla is colonial relic which is well-preserved. “Hanging Gardens”
